<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-29T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-29T22:00:00-05:00" n="1039" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111Sa1/12</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FHP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-29T22:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 30, 8 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Your telegrams December 22, 7 p.m., December 28, 6 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1039fn1">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office informs me that
                            unless <hi rend="italic">Sacramento</hi> leaves within twenty-four
                            hours, as notified to do through the American Consulate this afternoon,
                            both ship and crew will be interned. Consulate acting under the
                            instructions of Department, November 30, 7 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d1039fn2">Not printed.</note> is holding ship’s papers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_FHP1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>